## Running a Deploy (Agent Instructions)

The Agent should run `deploy.py` from the project root. Steps:

```bash
# Install Paramiko if not present
pip install paramiko requests

# Full deploy (code + migration check + verification)
python deploy.py

# Or run individual steps
python deploy.py --step migrate-status   # Just check pending migrations
python deploy.py --step verify-env       # Just verify .env is intact
python deploy.py --step smoke            # Just HTTP smoke test
python deploy.py --step tail-log         # Just tail Laravel log
```

The script handles the full flow:
1. Pre-flight check
2. Migration status (always, every deploy)
3. Git push (if not already pushed)
4. cPanel UAPI deploy trigger
5. `.env` integrity verification
6. Storage symlink check
7. Safety checks (@vite, @livewireScripts, PHP handler)
8. Migration run (with confirmation gate)
9. Cache rebuild
10. Laravel log check
11. HTTP smoke test

